last_episode_to_air.name: A Farewell to Kings
last_episode_to_air.overview: Writing the material took about six months, and recording the episode took about seventeen years in the studio to finish. Also Bug becomes a titan of industry.

name: Stone Quackers
overview: Stone Quackers revolves around two mischevious slacker ducks, Whit and Clay, along with their friends Barf and Dottie, plus the authority Officer Barry. They get into surreal misadventures, ranging from accidentally placing a bomb near an event where Officer Barry gets an award, to an odd homage to David Lynch's Blue Velvet.

episodes.name: One Last Bad Prank
episodes.overview: After being reprimanded by Dottie, the guys commit to one last prank before going straight. The situation quickly escalates out of control but no one knows why.

episodes.name: Stone Quackers V
episodes.overview: The ducks try to survive a hurricane. Meanwhile, Officer Barry deals with his family as the storm brings out the worst in them.

episodes.name: Stone Quackers II
episodes.overview: Barf goes on a rope swing; calamity ensues. Clay is healed by the power of dance.

episodes.name: Stone Quackers I
episodes.overview: Barry checks in on the ducks. Barf drives a tractor into the canal. The ducks go to a party and almost get an old acquaintance murdered.

episodes.name: Stone Quackers IV
episodes.overview: Whit and Clay discover a new sound to get them out of trouble. Barry stops disturbance between Dottie and her ex. Barf puts snake eggs in the house.

episodes.name: Stone Quackers III
episodes.overview: It's summer; the guys go skinny-dipping and create a whirlpool. Clay's sweat turns him into a sticky monster. Barf has to eat his hot dog outside, which has out-of-this-world consequences.

episodes.name: TwentyOneTwelve
episodes.overview: Dottie makes a move on Officer Barry while Whit and Clay deal with a newly-discovered mouse problem.

episodes.name: Blue Feathers
episodes.overview: Clay decides that they're going to play "bad guys" for the day and Dottie discovers evidence of a brutal crime.

episodes.name: Caress of Steel
episodes.overview: Based in the future, a galaxy wide war results in the union of all planets under the rule of the Cheeseburger Island.  Also Bug masters the culinary arts.

episodes.name: Power Windows
episodes.overview: The show’s producers didn’t want them to do another “concept” episode.  They ignored that advice and found large commercial success which allowed them to chart their own course moving forward.  Also Bug opens his mind.

episodes.name: Hemispheres
episodes.overview: According to a 1998 interview, the episode is based on Clay's frequent nightmares. The birds heard in Hemispheres were recorded outside near Ben Jones' Studios near the YMCA. Also Bug enjoys the serenity of a playground.

episodes.name: A Farewell to Kings
episodes.overview: Writing the material took about six months, and recording the episode took about seventeen years in the studio to finish. Also Bug becomes a titan of industry.
